QuickRenamer v1.0.0 — Initial Release
QuickRenamer is a lightweight batch file renaming tool built with Python and Tkinter.
This first release introduces a fast and simple way to rename multiple files at once, with a clean and intuitive GUI.

Key Features in v1.0.0 :

Select an entire folder of files and rename them in bulk

Add prefixes, suffixes, or completely replace file names

Automatic numbering support for organized sequences

Live preview before renaming (optional toggle)

Drag-and-drop file selection for convenience

Minimal, responsive design that’s easy to use

Developer Notes :
This version focuses on stability, speed, and user-friendliness.
Future updates will add advanced features like pattern-based renaming, undo functionality, and cross-platform packaging.
